         <t:abstract>
            <t:ab>The Canon of the church of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC4885Mualla">Muʿallaqa</t:placeName> is an introduction to the <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2384Taamme">Taʾammǝra
                                                  Māryām</t:ref>. It was purportedly translated from Arabic in <t:date when="1441"/> at the order of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob</t:persName>,
            but no Arabic version is known. It can be followed or preceded by
            <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3584Intro">Introductive
                                                  exhortation to the Taʾammǝra Māryām</t:ref>.</t:ab>
         </t:abstract>
